\int \frac{\sqrt{9 - x^2}}{x^2}dx = \int \cot^2 \theta \ d\theta = -\cot\theta - \theta + C
\int \frac{\sqrt{9 - x^2}}{x^2}dx = -\frac {\sqrt{9 - x^2}}{x} - \sin^{-1}\left(\frac{x}{3}\right) + C
\sqrt{9-x^2} = 3|\cos\theta| = 3\cos\theta \,
\sqrt{9-x^2} = |3||\cos\theta| = |3|\cos\theta
